5000|$|The EU <b>Ship</b> <b>Recycling</b> Regulation [...] {{entered into}} force on 30 December 2013. Although this {{regulation}} closely follows the Hong Kong convention, {{there are important}} differences. The Regulation sets {{out a number of}} requirements for European ships, European ship owners, <b>ship</b> <b>recycling</b> facilities willing to recycle European ships, and the relevant competent authorities or administrations. It also requires the Commission to adopt a number of acts implementing the Regulation (in particular the European List of <b>ship</b> <b>recycling</b> facilities authorized to recycle ships flying the Union flag). For the Inventory of Hazardous Materials required by the EU regulation, there are additional substances listed as prohibited.|$|E
